  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can invoke the power of law to embolden an ally to attack. If you cast a level 1+ spell and target an ally with the spell, that ally can take a Reaction immediately after the spell to make one weapon attack or Unarmed Strike against a creature of your choice that you can see.</p><p>If the spell targets more than one ally, you choose which ally.</p><p>At Cleric level 6, when an ally makes an attack with a Reaction granted by your Voice of Authority, you may make a single weapon attack with a weapon you are holding or Unarmed Strike as a part of any action you take until the end of your next turn.</p>",
